      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:3:1:3",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " سَأَلْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اللَّهِ عَنِ الْمَرْأَةِ مَا تَمْلِكُ مِنْ قَرَابَتِهَا قَالَ كُلَّ أَحَدٍ إِلَّا خَمْسَةً أَبَاهَا وَ أُمَّهَا وَ ابْنَهَا وَ ابْنَتَهَا وَ زَوْجَهَا ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Al Hajjal, from Asad Bin Abu Al Aa’la, from Abu Hamza who said, ",
          "‘I asked Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> about the woman, what she can own from her relatives?’ He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘Everyone except for five – her father, and her mother, and her son, and her daughter, and her husband’."
        ]
      }
    }
